There are 15 Affixes in total but different Equipment types can only use certain Affixes.

Each Runestone can generate an Affix with one of 3 levels. Affixes with different levels share the same drop rate of <color=#EA0000>33.33%</color>.

The Advanced Runestone has a <color=#EA0000>40%</color> of increasing a new Affix slot.

Equipment Enchantment can be performed up to 999 times daily. The remaining times reduce by 1 with each Runestone consumed, whether players replace the Affix or not, and reset at 4:00 daily (UTC-7).

1. Each combat costs 1 Fortune, whether players quit halfway or get defeated.
2. Players can have up to 3 <color=#CFB53B>Fortune</color>, which restores by 1 every 4 hrs.
3. Use the event item <color=#CFB53B>Dumpling</color> to restore Fortune. Dumplings can be purchased at Shop. After the event, the unused Dumplings will be converted to Stamina Elixirs at the ratio of 1:1, and then sent via in-game mail.

*Conversion rate from damage dealt to point: 1,000 DMG = 1 Point
*Combat rewards vary by phases, which are decided by the points.
Phase 1: 0≤ Points ＜500
Phase 2: 500≤ Points ＜1,000
Phase 3: 1,000≤ Points ＜5,000
Phase 4: 5,000≤ Points ＜10,000

<color=#FF6C6D>Chrono Gifts</color>
The event Chrono Gifts lasts for 21 days. It includes the Pack Shop and three Alternate Modes—each lasting for 7 days.
During the event, you can obtain Chrono Crystal from Alternate Modes or by buying packs. Collect Chrono Crystal to level up Chrono Gifts. When Chrono Gifts reach certain levels, you get corresponding rewards.

<color=#FF6C6D>Alternate Mode 1: Chrono Crusade</color>
You will play as the Witch to launch a crusade against your enemies. Complete daily quests to get Mana Coin, which can be used to level up the Witch to defeat stronger enemies. Defeat enemies to receive Chrono Crystal and other item rewards.
The combat will be turn-based, where both sides take turns to attack. Player goes first. When the enemy's HP reaches 0, player wins; when player's HP reaches 0, player loses.

<color=#FF6C6D>Alternate Mode 2: Chrono Puzzle</color>
Complete daily quests to get Witch Stamps, and use them to light up puzzle pieces. When a row/column is lit up, you get rewards. When all puzzle pieces are lit up, you get the final reward, then the puzzle refreshes and the rewards are reset.

<color=#FF6C6D>Alternate Mode 3: Chrono Maze</color>
Complete daily quests to get Magic Coupons, and use them to move the chess piece across the maze. Reaching different spots to get various rewards. When it returns to the starting point, a special reward can be obtained and the maze resets.

<color=#FF6C6D>Pack Shop</color>
The Pack Shop opens as soon as the event begins. It offers Chrono Crystal, special items for the Alternate Modes, and other items.

702476.text: While waiting for the grilled fish, the Witch decided to go to the market for a stroll.

702477.text: Already well-fed. It's time to go in search of the glowing shell!

702478.text: Just as Angling was trying to drag the shell away, an unexpected person appeared.

702479.text: After clearing up the misunderstanding, Ruda points out the direction of the sea elf. It's time to save Ardisia!

702480.text: Finally found the castle of the sea elf. Did not expect that the person who kidnapped Ardisia is the little girl met in the market.

702481.text: When the two are fighting hard, Ardisia sneaks out from the side and tries to rescue Angling from the sandpit......

702482.text: Just arrived. The sea creatures here seem extraordinarily "enthusiastic".
